---
import ServiceCityPage from '~/components/pages/ServiceCityPage.astro';
import { services, cities } from '~/data/service-city-config';
---

<ServiceCityPage service={services['code-corrections']} city={cities['holland-mi']}>
  <section class="container section-pad">
    <h2>The Code Issues We See Most in Holland Homes</h2>
    <p>
      Holland's older downtown and lakeshore housing stock shows the same recurring code findings: pre-1973 panels with
      double-tapped breakers, knob-and-tube remnants in attic spaces that got insulated decades later, and aluminum
      branch wiring in 1960s-70s subdivisions. None of those are inherently dangerous on day one, but inspectors and
      insurers flag them — and they should.
    </p>
    <p>
      If a Holland inspector or home-sale report has handed you a list, we'll walk it with you, separate the
      deal-breakers from the negotiables, and document the work in a packet your insurer or buyer will accept. Common
      code corrections in Holland often bundle with a <a href="/panel-upgrades-holland-mi">panel upgrade</a> — and if you're
      on Holland BPW, the panel side can stack with the <a href="/blog/holland-bpw-panel-rebate-guide"
        >$1,000 BPW rebate</a
      > when paired with electrification.
    </p>
  </section>
</ServiceCityPage>
